=== Privacy_Rights ===
The right to privacy is a protected right under the European Convention on Human Rights, Article 8. # diagram: echr_article_8.png

Digital ID systems fundamentally undermine this right.

You cannot exercise privacy rights when:
- Your location is trackable in real-time
- Your browsing history is tied to your identity
- Your face can be identified by any camera
- Your digital identity is required for basic services

This isn't about hiding wrongdoing.
It's about the fundamental right to live without constant surveillance.

Privacy isn't about having something to hide.
It's about having something to protect—your autonomy, your dignity, your freedom to think and act without being watched.

*   [But I have nothing to hide.]
    That's what people said about phone records before mass surveillance was revealed.
    It's what people said about social media before Cambridge Analytica.
    It's what people said about location data before it was sold to the highest bidder.
    
    You may have nothing to hide from this government.
    But this infrastructure will outlast this government.
    And power corrupts. Always.
